asset_contract.name: FLUF
asset_contract.description:
This is FLUF World…

A metaverse ecosystem of NFT character collectables and a global, creative community. From our genesis collection Flufs, to Thingies, Party Bears and more to come, we’re building a world that’s yours to shape, explore and call home. 

Flufs are the collection that started it all. 10,000 3D rabbit avatars, programmatically-generated from over 270 traits! Unique by at least three degrees of separation, Flufs are yours to trade, collect and customise through our growing Scenes & Sounds collection. 

But Flufs aren’t just furry faces... Metaverse-ready and full of surprises, they’re your ticket to a world of exclusive content, digital connectivity, IRL experiences and more.

Welcome to the Fluffle. 

---

name: Cerebro
description: Code name Cerebro. As a team member of the E.A.R.S Cyber Mystics, and a Mycelium Master, my function on the team is to have a holistic and connected understanding of everything going on during operations, sensing situations, knowing what is happening before it happens, and generally keeping the team safe. I wont go into detail as its pretty intense. On a lighter note, Im a bit of a team cheerleader, in a few ways. I actually won the Fluf World Hops Compet ition back in college. Eventually all Mycelium Mystics were banned as our abilities were an unfair advantage over normal fluf. But now I get to roll with the Cyber Mystics which is pretty much non stop excitement. And they still let me blow my whistle and and clown around now and then. You should check out how high I can jump though, its pretty incredible. Next time I will show you some videos of my college cheerleading days! If youre lucky I might take you out on a date and tell you my real name, but dont forget, I know what youre thinking.

A metaverse ecosystem of NFT character collectables and a global, creative community. From our genesis collection Flufs, to Thingies, Party Bears and more to come, we’re building a world that’s yours to shape, explore and call home. 

Flufs are the collection that started it all. 10,000 3D rabbit avatars, programmatically-generated from over 270 traits! Unique by at least three degrees of separation, Flufs are yours to trade, collect and customise through our growing Scenes & Sounds collection. 

But Flufs aren’t just furry faces... Metaverse-ready and full of surprises, they’re your ticket to a world of exclusive content, digital connectivity, IRL experiences and more.

Welcome to the Fluffle. 

---

A metaverse ecosystem of NFT character collectables and a global, creative community. From our genesis collection Flufs, to Thingies, Party Bears and more to come, we’re building a world that’s yours to shape, explore and call home. 

Flufs are the collection that started it all. 10,000 3D rabbit avatars, programmatically-generated from over 270 traits! Unique by at least three degrees of separation, Flufs are yours to trade, collect and customise through our growing Scenes & Sounds collection. 

But Flufs aren’t just furry faces... Metaverse-ready and full of surprises, they’re your ticket to a world of exclusive content, digital connectivity, IRL experiences and more.

Welcome to the Fluffle. 

---

[FLUF World: Burrows](https://opensea.io/collection/fluf-world-burrows)

name: Forest
description: As told in Fluf lore, during the great hibernation only a small number of Flufs remained awake to try help build a better world for their brothers and sisters. Carrots were in extremely short supply and an alternate food source to sustain the Fluffle was needed urgently. Forest had grown up on the edge of the woodlands and over time had taken to exploring the old growth canopy. This was an extremely dangerous place where Flufs were easy prey for Haast Eagles. As he grew older, Forest continued to travel further within the woods as he honed both his bushfluf and camoufluf skills. He was so good he could hop within 7 bunny lengths of an Eagle without detection. Little did he know that one day these skills would result in salvation for the Fluffle. It was indeed dire times for the Fluffle, famished and on the brink of starvation, Thumper sent Forest out in search of carrots yet again. Returning to his routes, Forest decided he would venture to the deepest depths of the woods on an all or nothing adventure. Just when he had all but given up hope, he discovered a mysterious glade surrounded in an odourous orange mist that smelt like sulphur. Peering through with his keen purple eyes, he spied carrot tops dotted throughout the clearing. Tentatively, he hopped across the sodden ground and tugged on a small one. To his surpise the carrot freed easily and it was the most orange of orange colours he had ever witnessed, the ultimate store of carotene. Forest took a nervous nibble of the carrot and to his complete surprise it split in two but remained the same size. Biting again the same thing happened. Could it be? Had Forest discovered carrot mecca!? Returning to the underground, Forest pas sed his bounty to Thumper. Extremely stubborn, Thumper was never easy to impress but news of this mitosis capable carrot had him beaming from ear to ear. Forest was immediately hailed a hero by the Fluffle and to this day is revered in Fluf lore as one of the greatest living Flufs to have ever Flufed for without his contribution, they would have surely not survived. He now spends his days teaching camoufluf to the next generation but is rarely seen.

name: Danny "Greased Lightning" Bucko
description: In the summer of 1958, local boy Danny Bucko and vacationing Sandy Bunny meet at the beach and fall in love. When summer comes to an end, Sandy, who is going back to Easter Island, frets that they may never meet again, but Danny tells her this is "only the beginning." Later on, at the start of Danny's senior year at Fluffle Society High School, he resumes his role as the leader of the T-Bunny greasers, consisting of his best friend Bugs, plus Roger, Thumper, and Buster. The Pinky Buttons, a clique of greaser bunnies, also arrive, consisting of leader Lola, Petunia, Bubbles, and Coco. After Sandy's parents decide not to return to Easter Island, she enrols at Fluffle Society and befriends Petunia, who is planning to drop out of school to become a beautician. Unaware of each other's presence at Fluffle Society, Danny and Sandy recount the events of their brief romance to their respective groups without saying each other's name. Sandy's version emphasizes the romance of the relationship, while Danny's version is more sexual. When Sandy finally mentions Danny's name, Lola arranges a surprise reunion for them, but Danny maintains his bad-bunny attitude in front of his friends and Sandy storms off in tears. Petunia invites the bunnies to a pyjama party, but Sandy falls ill from the sight of blood after Petunia pierces her long rabbit ears. While Sandy is out of the room, Lola starts to make fun of her. Sandy goes outside and starts to think of Danny, and how much she loves him even though he hurt her. The T-Bunnies come to Petunia's house so Danny can apologize to Sandy, but he leaves after they taunt him about her. Lola departs with Bugs to have **** with him, during which his condom breaks. They are disturbed by Peter, leader of the T-Bunnies' rival gang, the Squirrels, and his girlfriend Buttercup. Bugs unveils a used car, Greased Lightning, which he plans to restore for a drag race with the Squirrels. Sandy begins dating Baxter, a jock, and Danny turns to Coach Harvey to get into sports to impress her, eventually becoming a racer. He reunites with Sandy and they attempt to go on a date, but their friends crash it, and Bugs and Lola argue and split up. Left alone, Petunia is visited by a guardian angel who advises her to return to Fluffle Society after a mishap in beauty class leaves her with candy-pink fur. The school dance arrives, broadcast live on television and hosted by Vince Mortimer, who flirts with Bubbles. Lola and Bugs attempt to spite one another by bringing Peter and Buttercup as their dates. Danny and Sandy go together and dance well during the chaotic paw jive contest; just before it ends, Thumper pulls Sandy off the dance floor and Buttercup cuts in to win with Danny, causing Sandy to leave the event broken-hearted. Danny tries to make it up to Sandy by taking her to a drive-in theatre and giving her his carrot to eat, but Sandy leaves in anger after he forces himself on her. Meanwhile, Lola fears she is pregnant after missing a period and confides in Bubbles, but Bubbles tells Thumper and he inadvertently spreads the rumour to Bugs, the apparent father, though Bugs denies this to him. Lola starts to be laughed at by other bunnies, and she realizes that she is not as tough as she seems. On race day, Bugs suffers a concussion when hit by his own car door, so Danny takes the wheel. He and Peter race until Peter spins out and leaves humiliated, making Danny the victor. Sandy watches from afar, concluding she still loves Danny, and decides to change her attitude and look to impress him; she asks Petunia for help to achieve this. On the last day of school, Principal Greta Mae and her assistant Beatrix sob about the departing class. Lola discovers she is not pregnant and reunites with Bugs. Danny has lettered in track but is shocked when Sandy arrives dressed as a female T-Bunny. They confess their mutual love and reconcile. The class celebrates their graduation at the fair on school grounds. Sandy and Danny depart in a revamped Greased Lightning, which takes flight. Danny and Sandy then returned to Easter Island to live out their days bartending at their own Tiki Bar and lived happily ever after.
